    "macroSummary": "ISM Services shows resilient demand with new orders at 13-month highs, but prices spiked to October 2022 levels due to energy costs from Iran conflict, while employment contracted for first time in 4 months. The Fed-Bitcoin decoupling narrative gains traction as BTC profit-taking occurs below $70K despite corporate buying resumption. Geopolitical premium in oil creating stagflation pressures while Trump signals potential quick Iran resolution.",
